subSubSection.paragraph:
Medium sized (
6.5–9.5mm
) black species (
Fig. 2
), slightly larger than 

E. strigatus

, which can be distinguished from similar species by the black pilosity on vertical triangle (
Fig. 3
), the absence of a baso-ventral ridge in the metatibia (
Fig. 5B
), the shape of sternum IV with a pair of black spinose valves (
Fig. 6
) and the general morphology of male genitalia (
Fig. 7
).

